CVS-ID: pam_mktemp.spec 1.27

Updated the authorship, copyright, and licensing statements to use the

which would be too cumbersome with significant contributions by two authors).

Switched to using the heavily cut-down BSD license only.  The public domain
statements with a fallback to copyright+license would be a bit too cumbersome
now that there are significant contributions by two authors.

CVS-ID: pam_mktemp.c 1.15

Fix matchpathcon() invocation for user directory

CVS-ID: pam_mktemp.c 1.14

- Use ext2fs/ext2_fs.h instead of linux/ext2_fs.h to avoid potential
build problems with fresh kernel headers.
- Clear append-only flag from user directory iff the directory was
actually created.
- Replaced unsafe alloca(3) with malloc(3).
- Imported SELinux support from Sisyphus.

CVS-ID: pam_mktemp.spec 1.25

Imported SELinux support from Sisyphus

CVS-ID: Makefile 1.5
CVS-ID: pam_mktemp.c 1.13

Replace unsafe alloca(3) with malloc(3)

CVS-ID: pam_mktemp.c 1.12

Optimize ext2fs_chflags()

Do EXT2_IOC_SETFLAGS ioctl call iff new flags differ from old flags
returned earlier by EXT2_IOC_GETFLAGS ioctl call.

CVS-ID: pam_mktemp.c 1.11

Clear append-only flag from userdir iff the directory was actually created

On platforms where EXT2_APPEND_FL is supported, e.g. linux, always clear
this flag from just created user directory, even if setting this flag for
PRIVATE_PREFIX directory is not enabled.

CVS-ID: pam_mktemp.c 1.10

Include ext2fs/ext2_fs.h instead of linux/ext2_fs.h

Suggested by Christoph Hellwig in http://lkml.org/lkml/2008/9/10/105

CVS-ID: pam_mktemp.c 1.9

1.0.4:

No longer set the append-only flag on /tmp/.private (see the comment in
pam_mktemp.c for the rationale).

Placed the module into the public domain with fallback to a heavily cut-down
BSD license.

CVS-ID: pam_mktemp.spec 1.24

Placed the module into the public domain with fallback to a heavily cut-down

to standard set of six pam_sm_* functions.
- Changed Makefile to pass list of libraries to linker after regular
object files, to fix build with -Wl,--as-needed.
- Corrected specfile to make it build on x86_64.
